tissueExpression.summary: Most of the normal tissues showed moderate nuclear staining. Respiratory epithelium, fallopian tube and glial cells were strongly stained. Neuronal cells, lymphoid tissues and most mesenchymal cells were weakly stained or negative.

Most of the normal tissues showed moderate nuclear staining. Respiratory epithelium, fallopian tube and glial cells were strongly stained. Neuronal cells, lymphoid tissues and most mesenchymal cells were weakly stained or negative.
Gliomas and several cases of pancreatic, gastric, liver, renal and urothelial cancers showed weak to moderate nuclear immunoreactivity. Remaining cancer cells were negative.
